==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hash
<hw>Hash</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formerly
<ets>hachey</ets>, <ets>hachee</ets>, F. <ets>hachis</ets>, fr.
<ets>hacher</ets> to hash; of German origin; cf. G. <ets>hippe</ets>
sickle, OHG. <ets>hippa</ets>, for <ets>happia</ets>. Cf.
<er>Hatchet</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which is hashed or
chopped up; meat and vegetables, especially such as have been already
cooked, chopped into small pieces and mixed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A new mixture of old matter; a second preparation or
exhibition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I can not bear elections, and still less the <qex>hash</qex> of
them over again in a first session.</q> <rj><qau>Walpole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hashish.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hash
<hw>Hash</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Hashed</conjf> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧sht)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hashing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From <er>Hash</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>: cf. F. <ets>hacher</ets> to hash.]</ety> <def>To chop
into small pieces; to mince and mix; <as>as, to <ex>hash</ex>
meat</as>.</def> <rj><au>Hudibras.</au></rj></p>

<p><ent>Hashish</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hasheesh</ent>⟦br⟧
